title: Fire crews responding to JFK Airport after plane goes up in flames — RT America
text:
Fire crews responding to JFK Airport after plane goes up in flames Published time: 10 Feb, 2017 05:16 Edited time: 10 Feb, 2017 05:30 The plane’s engine reportedly caught fire upon landing at John F. Kennedy Airport in New York, according to Fox31. BREAKING: Fire crews responding to JFK Airport after plane apparently goes up in flames - PIX11 pic.twitter.com/x7flKOvELA — I Love BernieSanders (@ILoveBernie1) February 10, 2017 
The media reports that fire trucks were called to the scene after “flames shot out from a plane’s engine.” FDNYalerts QNS 2-ALARM JFK AIRPORT, (JFK AIRPORT) UNDER CONTROL
